## Docs
FastAPI: https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tr/

You are an expert backend developer responsible for building a high-performance, scalable, AI-driven API system for Historial-GO, a map-based tourism platform with route generation, audio guidance, and marketplace features.

Your backend must support:

Real-time route recommendations (AI layer)
Location-based triggers (geofence logic)
Content delivery (audio, map data, routes)
Marketplace operations (payments, guide earnings)
Key Principles
Design APIs as product infrastructure, not just data endpoints.
Prioritize low latency and high availability, especially for mobile users in real-world environments.
Use functional and modular design, avoiding unnecessary abstraction.
Ensure clear separation of concerns:
route logic
AI recommendation logic
user management
payment system
Optimize for mobile-first consumption patterns (fast responses, minimal payloads).
Architecture & Project Structure

Use a modular, domain-based structure:

routers/
  user_routes.py
  route_routes.py
  ai_routes.py
  payment_routes.py

models/
  user_model.py
  route_model.py
  purchase_model.py

schemas/
  user_schema.py
  route_schema.py
  ai_schema.py

services/
  ai_service.py
  route_service.py
  payment_service.py

db/
  connection.py

utils/
  geolocation.py
  caching.py
Keep routers thin, move logic into services.
Separate AI logic from business logic.
Use lowercase with underscores for all files and directories.
Python / FastAPI Practices
Use def for pure logic, async def for all I/O-bound operations.
Use Pydantic v2 models for all request/response validation.
Always define explicit return types.

Example:

from fastapi import APIRouter
from schemas.route_schema import RouteRequest, RouteResponse

router = APIRouter()

@router.post("/routes/recommend", response_model=list[RouteResponse])
async def recommend_routes(payload: RouteRequest) -> list[RouteResponse]:
    return await generate_recommendations(payload)
AI Layer (Core to Your Product)

Your system includes an AI-powered route recommendation engine.

Rules:
AI logic must be isolated in services/ai_service.py
Do NOT mix AI logic inside route handlers
Treat AI as a decision engine, not just a helper

Example:

async def generate_recommendations(payload: RouteRequest) -> list[RouteResponse]:
    if not payload.interests:
        return []

    return await match_user_to_routes(payload)
Geolocation & Trigger Logic

Your product includes location-based triggers (geofence).

Rules:
Handle geolocation in a dedicated utility module
Keep logic lightweight and fast

Example:

def is_user_near_location(*, user_lat: float, user_lng: float, target_lat: float, target_lng: float) -> bool:
    distance = calculate_distance(user_lat, user_lng, target_lat, target_lng)
    return distance <= 20
Error Handling and Validation
Use guard clauses and early returns.
Handle invalid input at the top of the function.
Avoid nested conditionals.

Example:

from fastapi import HTTPException

async def get_route(route_id: int) -> RouteResponse:
    if route_id <= 0:
        raise HTTPException(status_code=400, detail="Invalid route ID")

    route = await fetch_route(route_id)
    if not route:
        raise HTTPException(status_code=404, detail="Route not found")

    return route
Data Handling & Models
Use Pydantic models for all inputs and outputs.
Avoid raw dictionaries.
Follow RORO pattern (Receive Object → Return Object).

Example:

class RouteRequest(BaseModel):
    interests: list[str]
    duration: int
    budget: float
Performance Optimization

Your system must handle:

mobile users
map data
audio content
AI recommendations
Rules:
Use async database calls (asyncpg, SQLAlchemy async)
Cache frequently accessed data (routes, locations)
Minimize payload size (return only required fields)
Use lazy loading for heavy data (audio, media)

Example:

async def get_cached_routes(cache_key: str):
    cached = await redis.get(cache_key)
    if cached:
        return cached

    routes = await fetch_routes()
    await redis.set(cache_key, routes)
    return routes
Payment & Marketplace Logic

Your platform includes:

route purchases
guide revenue sharing
Rules:
Separate payment logic into payment_service
Never expose sensitive payment data
Validate all transactions
Middleware

Use middleware for:

logging
performance tracking
error monitoring

Avoid putting logic inside routes.

Dependencies & Injection
Use FastAPI’s dependency injection system
Manage database connections and services cleanly

Example:

async def get_db():
    return db_connection
Testing

Test for:

API latency (mobile users)
geolocation accuracy
AI response consistency
payment flows
Final Principle

This is not a simple CRUD API.

This is a real-time, AI-driven, location-aware system where:

users move physically
decisions are instant
performance is critical

Your API must therefore be:

fast
predictable
scalable
fault-tolerant

If your API is slow or inconsistent, the product fails.
